  "reviews": [We've actually stayed here twice, and both visits had one thing in common—we had just purchased a new camper. The campground sits conveniently between our RV dealer and home, making it the perfect place for a "shake-out trip." Instead of discovering a problem three states away, we could test every system, make a shopping run if we forgot something, and be close enough to home if needed.<br>
One of the biggest advantages of this campground is the shopping. Within just a few minutes you'll find Target, Lowe's, Home Depot, Walmart, Costco, Camping World, grocery stores, and practically anything else you might need for a new RV. During one stay we even had Amazon packages delivered directly to the campground office, where staff placed them in a designated pickup area on the porch for guests.]
